http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Vellappally-arrested-granted-bail/article13982053.ece

The Ernakulam rural police on Monday recorded the arrest of Sree Narayana Dharma Paripalana (SNDP) Yogam general secretary Vellappally Natesan in connection with the alleged hate speech case against him.Mr. Natesan appeared before T.B. Vijayan, circle inspector, at Aluva around 10.30 a.m.Official sources said that Mr. Natesan reportedly told the police that he did not intend to create any communal tension through his speech and alleged that the State government was attempting to settle political scores.Later, he was taken for a medical examination and produced before the Judicial First Class Magistrate Court, which granted him bail. The bail was granted upon executing a bond of Rs.25,000 along with a solvent surety of two persons.Earlier, the Kerala High Court had directed Mr. Natesan to surrender before the investigating officer on or before January 12 in connection with the case.Talking to media persons, Mr. Natesan said the speech was made with the good intention of ensuring justice to all. He criticised KPCC president V.M. Sudheeran for using political power to frame false cases with the intention of defaming him.The Aluva police had registered a case against Mr. Natesan under Section 153 (A) of Indian Penal Code upon a compliant filed by Mr. Sudheeran.